abstract: A meeting of U.S. government officials to discuss further curbs on exports to Huawei and China is still on for Thursday, two sources said, despite pushback from President Donald Trump against the restrictions.
snippet: A meeting of U.S. government officials to discuss further curbs on exports to Huawei and China is still on for Thursday, two sources said, despite pushback from President Donald Trump against the restrictions.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A meeting of U.S. government officials to discuss further curbs on exports to Huawei and China is still on for Thursday, two sources said, despite pushback from President Donald Trump against the restrictions.
headline_main: U.S. Meeting on Huawei, China Policy Still On for Thursday Despite Trump Tweets: Sources
headline_print_headline: U.S. Meeting on Huawei, China Policy Still On for Thursday Despite Trump Tweets: Sources

abstract: The debate over fresh U.S. sanctions aimed at forcing out Venezuela's Nicolás Maduro played out Wednesday across the crisis-stricken nation — including a bustling Caracas bus terminal.
snippet: The debate over fresh U.S. sanctions aimed at forcing out Venezuela's Nicolás Maduro played out Wednesday across the crisis-stricken nation — including a bustling Caracas bus terminal.
lead_paragraph: CARACAS, Venezuela — The debate over fresh U.S. sanctions aimed at forcing out Venezuela's Nicolás Maduro played out Wednesday across the crisis-stricken nation — including a bustling Caracas bus terminal.
headline_main: Venezuelans React to U.S. Sanctions Targeting Maduro
headline_print_headline: Venezuelans React to U.S. Sanctions Targeting Maduro

abstract: There's a common thread among the 11 felons who found favor with President Donald Trump this week — all who were pardoned or set free had advocates among the president’s wealthy friends and political allies.

headline_main: Trump Picks Pardon Requests From Wealthy Pals and GOP Donors

abstract: Even as President Donald Trump renewed his public attacks on the Justice Department on Wednesday, there was little outward worry from either end of Pennsylvania Avenue that Attorney General William Barr would follow through on his private threat to resign over presidential meddling.
snippet: Even as President Donald Trump renewed his public attacks on the Justice Department on Wednesday, there was little outward worry from either end of Pennsylvania Avenue that Attorney General William Barr would follow through on his private threat t...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Even as President Donald Trump renewed his public attacks on the Justice Department on Wednesday, there was little outward worry from either end of Pennsylvania Avenue that Attorney General William Barr would follow through on his private threat to resign over presidential meddling.
headline_main: As Trump Ups Attacks on Justice Dept, Barr Remains in Post
headline_print_headline: As Trump Ups Attacks on Justice Dept, Barr Remains in Post

abstract: President Donald Trump on Wednesday named U.S. ambassador to Germany Richard Grenell, a strong supporter of his policies, to be acting director of national intelligence.
snippet: President Donald Trump on Wednesday named U.S. ambassador to Germany Richard Grenell, a strong supporter of his policies, to be acting director of national intelligence.
lead_paragraph: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. — President Donald Trump on Wednesday named U.S. ambassador to Germany Richard Grenell, a strong supporter of his policies, to be acting director of national intelligence.
headline_main: Trump Names U.S. Envoy to Germany Acting Director of National Intelligence
headline_print_headline: Trump Names U.S. Envoy to Germany Acting Director of National Intelligence

abstract: Former Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid on Wednesday said it was possible the crowded Democratic primary race was headed toward a contentious convention fight and downplayed the political dangers of a scenario many party leaders are dreading.
snippet: Former Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid on Wednesday said it was possible the crowded Democratic primary race was headed toward a contentious convention fight and downplayed the political dangers of a scenario many party leaders are dreading.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Former Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid on Wednesday said it was possible the crowded Democratic primary race was headed toward a contentious convention fight and downplayed the political dangers of a scenario many party leaders are dreading.
headline_main: Harry Reid: Brokered Convention 'Not the End of the World'
headline_print_headline: Harry Reid: Brokered Convention 'Not the End of the World'

abstract: But if hard-liners in the U.S. administration were hoping for a united, anti-China message from Washington, that goal has been undermined by President Trump.
snippet: But if hard-liners in the U.S. administration were hoping for a united, anti-China message from Washington, that goal has been undermined by President Trump.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — Tariffs and the trade war. Espionage and Huawei. Hong Kong, Taiwan and the South China Sea.

abstract: The move places a loyalist atop the intelligence agencies that the president has long battled.
snippet: The move places a loyalist atop the intelligence agencies that the president has long battled.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Wednesday named Richard Grenell, the ambassador to Germany who quickly antagonized the establishment after arriving in Berlin in 2018, to be the acting director of national intelligence overseeing the nation’s 17 spy agencies.

abstract: New York City's police commissioner during the Sept. 11 attacks said Wednesday he started crying when President Donald Trump pardoned him for felony convictions that put him behind bars for three years, aware he got a break other ex-convicts never see.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — New York City's police commissioner during the Sept. 11 attacks said Wednesday he started crying when President Donald Trump pardoned him for felony convictions that put him behind bars for three years, aware he got a break other ex-convicts never see.
headline_main: Ex-NYC Police Commish Kerik Says He Cried at Being Pardoned
headline_print_headline: Ex-NYC Police Commish Kerik Says He Cried at Being Pardoned
